kubectl get priorityclass

matching this field:
in priority-class.yaml:
metadata:
  name: high-priority

in pod-definition.yaml:
spec:
  priorityClassNAme: high-priority

default value is 0 if not specified, if modify, nmust create a new priority class and assign the global default property to true. 
note that in this case it can only be defined in a single priority class.

to assign higher priority workload to a full pod, the default value of 'preemptionPolicy: PreemptLowerPriority' means stopping the lower ones and put higher ones in;
otherwise specify the value as preemptionPolicy: never

